    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.66,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.98,
      "end": 15.36,
      "text": "For more information and to find out how you can volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 16.86,
      "end": 20.94,
      "text": "Recorded by Leanne Takei in Sitka, Alaska.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 22.96,
      "end": 26.9,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, the Fly and the Draft meal.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 27.82,
      "end": 33.5,
      "text": "A fly sat on one of the shafts of a cart and said to the meal who was pulling it,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 33.96,
      "end": 40.28,
      "text": "How slow you are, do mend your pace, or I shall have to use my sting as a goad.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 41.14,
      "end": 43.72,
      "text": "The meal was not in the least disturbed.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 44.96,
      "end": 49.66,
      "text": "Behind me in the cart said he, sits my master.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 50.52,
      "end": 55.16,
      "text": "He holds the reins and flicks me with his whip, and him I obey,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 55.16,
      "end": 62.4,
      "text": "But I don't want any of your impertinence. I know when I may doddle and when I may not.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 64.94,
      "end": 67.62,
      "text": "End of the fly and the draft meal.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
